  <!-- EN: grand altar -->
  <Altar_Grand.label>巨型祭壇</Altar_Grand.label>
  <!-- EN: A grand platform that plays a role in ideoligious rituals. -->
  <Altar_Grand.description>一座巨型平台，可以作為儀式的中心。</Altar_Grand.description>
  
  <!-- EN: large altar -->
  <Altar_Large.label>大型祭壇</Altar_Large.label>
  <!-- EN: A large platform that plays a role in ideoligious rituals. -->
  <Altar_Large.description>一座大型平台，可以作為儀式的中心。</Altar_Large.description>
  
  <!-- EN: medium altar -->
  <Altar_Medium.label>中型祭壇</Altar_Medium.label>
  <!-- EN: A medium platform that plays a role in ideoligious rituals. -->
  <Altar_Medium.description>一座中型平台，可以作為儀式的中心。</Altar_Medium.description>
  
  <!-- EN: small altar -->
  <Altar_Small.label>小型祭壇</Altar_Small.label>
  <!-- EN: A small platform that plays a role in ideoligious rituals. -->
  <Altar_Small.description>一座小型平台，可以作為儀式的中心。</Altar_Small.description>
  
  <!-- EN: biosculpter pod -->
  <BiosculpterPod.label>塑體艙</BiosculpterPod.label>
  <!-- EN: An immersion pod full of bioactive gel. It can perform a variety of biological alterations including age reversal and pleasure-giving.\n\nThe pod biotunes to its user at the end of a cycle. While biotuned, it cannot be used by anyone else, but cycles will complete 25% more quickly. Biotuning resets if the pod is unused for 80 days.\n\nThe pod consumes 200W of power while working, but only 50W on standby. -->
  <BiosculpterPod.description>一個注滿生物活化凝膠的全身艙。它可以進行各種生理改造，例如逆齡和樂活。\n\n塑體艙會在療程完結後針對其使用者進行生物配對。當配對過後，其他人將不能使用，但後續療程將加快25%。若80天內未被使用，配對將被重置。\n\n塑體艙在工作時會消耗200W，但待命時只消耗50W。</BiosculpterPod.description>
  <!-- EN: medic -->
  <BiosculpterPod.comps.CompBiosculpterPod_MedicCycle.label>醫療</BiosculpterPod.comps.CompBiosculpterPod_MedicCycle.label>
  <!-- EN: Heal all fresh wounds, blood loss, and one random infectious disease. -->
  <BiosculpterPod.comps.CompBiosculpterPod_MedicCycle.description>癒合所有新傷口，失血，和隨機一處感染病症。</BiosculpterPod.comps.CompBiosculpterPod_MedicCycle.description>
  <!-- EN: bioregeneration -->
  <BiosculpterPod.comps.CompBiosculpterPod_RegenerationCycle.label>再生</BiosculpterPod.comps.CompBiosculpterPod_RegenerationCycle.label>
  <!-- EN: Heal all fresh wounds, heal one random permanent injury, and restore small missing body parts like fingers and toes. -->
  <BiosculpterPod.comps.CompBiosculpterPod_RegenerationCycle.description>癒合所有新傷口，治療隨機一處永久傷口，和再生小型缺肢，例如手指和腳趾等。</BiosculpterPod.comps.CompBiosculpterPod_RegenerationCycle.description>
  <!-- EN: age reversal -->
  <BiosculpterPod.comps.CompBiosculpterPod_AgeReversalCycle.label>逆齡</BiosculpterPod.comps.CompBiosculpterPod_AgeReversalCycle.label>
  <!-- EN: Reverse {DURATION} of aging. -->
  <BiosculpterPod.comps.CompBiosculpterPod_AgeReversalCycle.description>把年齡倒退{DURATION}。</BiosculpterPod.comps.CompBiosculpterPod_AgeReversalCycle.description>
  <!-- EN: pleasure -->
  <BiosculpterPod.comps.CompBiosculpterPod_PleasureCycle.label>樂活</BiosculpterPod.comps.CompBiosculpterPod_PleasureCycle.label>
  <!-- EN: Temporarily reshape the nervous system to deliver elevated levels of happiness for a time. -->
  <BiosculpterPod.comps.CompBiosculpterPod_PleasureCycle.description>暫時改造神經系統，使人短時間提升快樂。</BiosculpterPod.comps.CompBiosculpterPod_PleasureCycle.description>
  
  <!-- EN: burnbong -->
  <Burnbong.label>煙筒</Burnbong.label>
  <!-- EN: A wood structure packed with smokeleaf. It can be ignited during a ritual and produce a huge amount of smokeleaf smoke for a few hours, after which it is destroyed. -->
  <Burnbong.description>一台裝有菸草的木製設備。它可以在儀式中被點燃並產生大量菸煙持續幾小時，用後會被銷毀。</Burnbong.description>
  
  <!-- EN: cannibal platter -->
  <CannibalPlatter.label>人肉盤</CannibalPlatter.label>
  <!-- EN: An area of floor covered with pre-chopped and arranged human meat ready for a cannibal feast. -->
  <CannibalPlatter.description>為人肉盛宴預備的一堆切好的人肉。</CannibalPlatter.description>
  
  <!-- EN: christmas tree -->
  <ChristmasTree.label>聖誕樹</ChristmasTree.label>
  <!-- EN: A celebratory tree decorated with ornaments and lights traditionally made as part of Christmas celebrations. -->
  <ChristmasTree.description>一棵慶典用的樹，上面掛有裝飾物和燈。是傳統聖誕慶典的一部份。</ChristmasTree.description>
  
  <!-- EN: darktorch -->
  <Darktorch.label>暗火把</Darktorch.label>
  <!-- EN: A specially-treated wooden torch that produces a dim light over a large area. People who prefer darklight work best with this light source. Can be automatically refueled with wood. Produces a small amount of heat. -->
  <Darktorch.description>特殊處理過的木製火把，為附近區域發出暗光。偏好在暗燈環境工作的人會喜歡這個光源。需要定期補充木頭燃料。會產生少量的熱能。</Darktorch.description>
  
  <!-- EN: fungus darktorch -->
  <DarktorchFungus.label>菇菌暗火把</DarktorchFungus.label>
  <!-- EN: A specially-treated fungus torch that produces a dim light over a large area. People who prefer darklight work best with this light source. Can be automatically refueled with raw fungus. Produces a small amount of heat. -->
  <DarktorchFungus.description>特殊處理過的菇菌製火把，為附近區域發出暗光。偏好在暗燈環境工作的人會喜歡這個光源。需要定期補充菇菌燃料。會產生少量的熱能。</DarktorchFungus.description>
  
  <!-- EN: effigy -->
  <Effigy.label>偶像</Effigy.label>
  <!-- EN: A rough wooden frame in the shape of a human, ready to be burned as part of a ritual. -->
  <Effigy.description>一個粗糙的木製人型像，用於火祭。</Effigy.description>
  
  <!-- EN: ideogram -->
  <Ideogram.label>符號</Ideogram.label>
  <!-- EN: A large image drawn on the ground and reinforced with metal edges. It is used as a focus for rituals. -->
  <Ideogram.description>畫在地上的巨大的圖案，並以金屬包覆保護。可以作為儀式的中心。</Ideogram.description>
  
  <!-- EN: incense shrine -->
  <IncenseShrine.label>香爐</IncenseShrine.label>
  <!-- EN: A collection of packed incense containers. It can be ignited and produce a powerful incense effect as a focus for rituals. It is destroyed after it burns down. -->
  <IncenseShrine.description>一組香爐。它可以在儀式中被點燃並產生強力煙香效果。用後會被銷毀。</IncenseShrine.description>
  
  <!-- EN: neural supercharger -->
  <NeuralSupercharger.label>神經超載器</NeuralSupercharger.label>
  <!-- EN: A neuron-sensitizing device that can deliver one neural supercharge each day. A person with a neural supercharge will think and learn faster, but will also consume more food. The effect wears off in one day. Neural superchargers consume a lot of electricity. -->
  <NeuralSupercharger.description>神經強化裝置，可以每天為人進行神經超載。獲得神經超載的人會加速思考和學習，但亦會加快飢餓。效果持續一天。神經超載消耗大量電力。</NeuralSupercharger.description>
  <!-- EN: Get neural supercharge -->
  <NeuralSupercharger.comps.CompNeuralSupercharger.jobString>神經超載</NeuralSupercharger.comps.CompNeuralSupercharger.jobString>
  
  <!-- EN: pyre -->
  <Pyre.label>篝火</Pyre.label>
  <!-- EN: A wooden tower for ritual burning. -->
  <Pyre.description>用於火祭的一疊木頭。</Pyre.description>
  
  <!-- EN: ritual spot -->
  <RitualSpot.label>儀式點</RitualSpot.label>
  <!-- EN: A spot for carrying out certain kinds of rituals. -->
  <RitualSpot.description>可以進行部份儀式的地方。</RitualSpot.description>
  
  <!-- EN: sacrificial flag -->
  <SacrificialFlag.label>獻祭旗</SacrificialFlag.label>
  <!-- EN: A flag representing enemies, ready to be burned as part of a ritual. -->
  <SacrificialFlag.description>代表著敵人的旗幟，用於火祭。</SacrificialFlag.description>
  
  <!-- EN: sleep accelerator -->
  <SleepAccelerator.label>睡眠加速器</SleepAccelerator.label>
  <!-- EN: A bedside device that accelerates the sleeper's circadian rhythm. This speeds up sleep, but consumes a lot of electricity and also causes increased hunger. It must be placed directly adjacent to and facing the head of the bed. Placing more than one sleep accelerator near the same bed has no effect. -->
  <SleepAccelerator.description>一個可以加速使用者生理節奏的床邊裝置。雖然可以加速睡眠，但亦消耗大量電力並加速飢餓。必須放置在床頭旁邊。一張床只能受到一個睡眠加速器的影響。</SleepAccelerator.description>
  
</LanguageData>